remarks: .4 darter debated on if it was a blunt nose darter
Maybe strips bass. Need to review picture
Too young to id. Either blackbanded or dusky darter
Taxon ID code not available. This is a juvenile largemouth bass Micropterus salmoides
Looks like notropis stilbius with deer tracks but no tail spot
Has the same fin characteristics and mouth of fundulus but it is so small and young it is hard to ID down to species
Species is esox niger (Chain Pickerel) because it has a vertical black tear drop.
Brown olive darter. 11 light brown midlateral blotches. 8 ill defined dusky saddles. Black stripe going through eye to nose and a black stripe going down from eye.
The slight red spot behind ear makes me distinguish it from the redear sunfish. Warmouth young of the year have dark vertical bars and pale centers as pictured here.
The fins look much like that of a shoal bass (Micropterus cataractae) but we are not in shoal bass range. Most likely a largemouth bass (Micropterus salmoides) juvenile.
May be blue headed chub. Further ID
